rips and want a superior ownership experience.', 'Ebike Price Drops', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '63-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-01 10:12:38', '2015-06-01 17:12:38', '', 63, 'http://overvolted.com/63-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(65, 1, '2015-06-01 10:12:47', '2015-06-01 17:12:47', 'In the electric bike world, there is a pretty significant price premium given to branded electric bikes sold through traditional retail channels, and this markup serves to pay for some very important costs that every ebike owner needs to understand: 1) profit for the retailer, 2) money for the manufacturer to set aside for future warranty claims, and 3) marketing and distribution costs. If ebike manufacturers weren''t able to pass on these costs to their ebike customers, then the industry''s important retail channel, which crucially allows ebike owners to test-drive demo bikes in a store to determine the best product to buy, would not exist at all. The recent growth in the electric bike retail channel paired with the overall growth in ebike sales volume seems to be giving the industry an increased scale, and the cost efficiencies that come with that scale are showing themselves in lower prices for certain ebikes, and these price drops will only drive the ebike market to hit higher and higher sales volumes, which promises to benefit ebike buyers and manufacturers alike.\r\n\r\nIn the high-end section of the market, we''ve recently seen popular models like the <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/haibike/xduro-rx-29/" target="_blank">Haibike XDURO RX 29"</a> get a ~$500 price drop, from $3950 to $3499. On the lower-end, we''ve seen the introduction of various models priced from $1,499 to $2,199, including the <a href="http://www.genze.com/model/genze-e-bike/" target="_blank">Genze E-Bike</a> and the <a href="http://ejoebike.com/2015-koda" target="_blank">e-JOE Koda</a>. The increased availability of well-designed ebikes in the $1,000-$2,500 range will be an important source of growth in the ebike market and will primarily target first-time ebike buyers, and the falling prices for high-end ebikes from Haibike might reasonable be expected to increase sales volume for those who use their ebikes for the majority of their trips and want a superior ownership experience.', 'Ebike Price Drops', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '63-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-01 10:12:47', '2015-06-01 17:12:47', '', 63, 'http://overvolted.com/63-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
