(80, 1, '2015-06-04 18:52:13', '2015-06-05 01:52:13', 'Though Haibike has been teasing the US market with photos of its XDURO Fullcarbon and a promised release this spring, it''s only just become available for <a href="http://www.motostrano.com/Haibike-XDURO-FullCarbon-E-Bike-p/18-15-6102.htm" target="_blank">pre-order from an actual shop (Motostrano)</a>, so we imagine that it''s only a matter of weeks before the first few examples make their way over to our fair shores.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike1.jpg" alt="Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-77" />\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n\r\n<figure><img src="http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike1.jpg" alt="Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-77"><figcaption>The Haibike XDURO Fullcarbon (European model shown).</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nThe Bosch-powered ebike sports a rare combination of a carbon fiber frame paired with a full suspension. Trail riders with $9,500 burning a hole in their pockets ought to get ready to drop some serious cash, because this bike promises to be quite the off-road performer, especially considering the almost <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/?s=haibike+xduro" target="_blank">universal acclaim</a> that is showered upon Haibike offroad models by influential ebike reviewer <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/" target="_blank">Court Rye</a>.\r\n\r\nThere''s no word yet on the final weight that we can expect for the Fullcarbon, but since the aluminum-framed full suspension <a href="http://www.currietech.com/haibike/haibike-xduro-fs-rx-27-5-d-4" target="_blank">Haibike XDURO FS RX</a> weighs 48lbs, we''d put good money on the Fullcarbon tipping the scales somewhere just above 40lbs.', 'Haibike Now Taking Pre-Orders For New XDURO Fullcarbon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '69-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-04 18:52:13', '2015-06-05 01:52:13', '', 69, 'http://overvolted.com/69-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(82, 1, '2015-06-04 18:55:58', '2015-06-05 01:55:58', 'Though Haibike has been teasing the US market with photos of its XDURO Fullcarbon and a promised release this spring, it''s only just become available for <a href="http://www.motostrano.com/Haibike-XDURO-FullCarbon-E-Bike-p/18-15-6102.htm" target="_blank">pre-order from an actual shop (Motostrano)</a>, so we imagine that it''s only a matter of weeks before the first few examples make their way over to our fair shores.\r\n\r\n<figure><img src="http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike1.jpg" alt="Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-77"><figcaption>The Haibike XDURO Fullcarbon Ultimate.</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nThe Bosch-powered ebike sports a rare combination of a carbon fiber frame paired with a full suspension. Trail riders with $9,500 burning a hole in their pockets ought to get ready to drop some serious cash, because this bike promises to be quite the off-road performer, especially considering the almost <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/?s=haibike+xduro" target="_blank">universal acclaim</a> that is showered upon Haibike offroad models by influential ebike reviewer <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/" target="_blank">Court Rye</a>.\r\n\r\nThere''s no word yet on the final weight that we can expect for the Fullcarbon, but since the aluminum-framed full suspension <a href="http://www.currietech.com/haibike/haibike-xduro-fs-rx-27-5-d-4" target="_blank">Haibike XDURO FS RX</a> weighs 48lbs, we''d put good money on the Fullcarbon tipping the scales somewhere just above 40lbs.', 'Haibike Now Taking Pre-Orders For New XDURO Fullcarbon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '69-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-04 18:55:58', '2015-06-05 01:55:58', '', 69, 'http://overvolted.com/69-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(83, 1, '2015-06-04 18:57:50', '2015-06-05 01:57:50', 'Though Haibike has been teasing the US market with photos of its XDURO Fullcarbon and a promised release this spring, it''s only just become available for <a href="http://www.motostrano.com/Haibike-XDURO-FullCarbon-E-Bike-p/18-15-6102.htm" target="_blank">pre-order from an actual shop (Motostrano)</a>, so we imagine that it''s only a matter of weeks before the first few examples make their way over to our fair shores.\r\n\r\n<figure><img src="http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike1.jpg" alt="Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-77"><figcaption>The &euro;13,499 Haibike XDURO Fullcarbon Ultimate.</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nThe Bosch-powered ebike sports a rare combination of a carbon fiber frame paired with a full suspension. Trail riders with $9,500 burning a hole in their pockets ought to get ready to drop some serious cash, because this bike promises to be quite the off-road performer, especially considering the almost <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/?s=haibike+xduro" target="_blank">universal acclaim</a> that is showered upon Haibike offroad models by influential ebike reviewer <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/" target="_blank">Court Rye</a>.\r\n\r\nThere''s no word yet on the final weight that we can expect for the Fullcarbon, but since the aluminum-framed full suspension <a href="http://www.currietech.com/haibike/haibike-xduro-fs-rx-27-5-d-4" target="_blank">Haibike XDURO FS RX</a> weighs 48lbs, we''d put good money on the Fullcarbon tipping the scales somewhere just above 40lbs.', 'Haibike Now Taking Pre-Orders For New XDURO Fullcarbon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '69-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-04 18:57:50', '2015-06-05 01:57:50', '', 69, 'http://overvolted.com/69-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(84, 1, '2015-06-04 19:02:39', '2015-06-05 02:02:39', 'Though Haibike has been teasing the US market with photos of its XDURO Fullcarbon and a promised release this spring, it''s only just become available for <a href="http://www.motostrano.com/Haibike-XDURO-FullCarbon-E-Bike-p/18-15-6102.htm" target="_blank">pre-order from an actual shop (Motostrano)</a>, so we imagine that it''s only a matter of weeks before the first few examples make their way over to our fair shores. The bike, with a US MSRP of $9,500, appears to be the Fullcarbon RX trim level, which comes with Mavic wheels and shocks from RockShox and Fox (front and rear, respectively).\r\n\r\n<figure><img src="http://overvolted.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike1.jpg" alt="Haibike-xDuro-Full-Carbon-Ultimate-2015-Bosch-eBike" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-77"><figcaption>The &euro;13,499 Haibike XDURO Fullcarbon Ultimate.</figcaption></figure>\r\n\r\nThe Bosch-powered ebike sports a rare combination of a carbon fiber frame paired with a full suspension. Trail riders with $9,500 burning a hole in their pockets ought to get ready to drop some serious cash, because this bike promises to be quite the off-road performer, especially considering the almost <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/?s=haibike+xduro" target="_blank">universal acclaim</a> that is showered upon Haibike offroad models by influential ebike reviewer <a href="http://electricbikereview.com/" target="_blank">Court Rye</a>.\r\n\r\nThere''s no word yet on the final weight that we can expect for the Fullcarbon, but since the aluminum-framed full suspension <a href="http://www.currietech.com/haibike/haibike-xduro-fs-rx-27-5-d-4" target="_blank">Haibike XDURO FS RX</a> weighs 48lbs, we''d put good money on the Fullcarbon tipping the scales somewhere just above 40lbs.', 'Haibike Now Taking Pre-Orders For New XDURO Fullcarbon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '69-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-04 19:02:39', '2015-06-05 02:02:39', '', 69, 'http://overvolted.com/69-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
